Description: This is a 2018 Fender Players Series Alder Body in Polar White (Previously listed as Standard Series, Ah body and Arctic White) body is clean and has no dents or nicks in paint. The neck and body were purchased separate and pickups were professionally installed at a Fender Dealership. Loaded with a 920 D Pickup upgrade. Seymour Duncan Vintage Stack Pickups 11208-33 The Seymour Duncan ST50-1s Little '59/Vintage Pickup Set includes the ST59-1b lead (bridge) pickup paired with the STK-T1n rhythm (neck) pickup. The Seymour Duncan ST59-1b is a P.A.F.-voiced single-coil-sized humbucker bridge pickup for Telecaster guitars. Great for country, jazz, blues, funk, classic rock and heavy rock. The ST59-1b lead pickup is a hybrid. Designed for the Telecaster player who wants to rock, this little beast delivers a warm, smooth tone, reminiscent of an old '59 patent applied for humbucker mixed together with a healthy dose of beefed up twang. The Seymour Duncan STK-T1n is a vintage-voiced humbucker. Perfect for traditional country, country pop, chicken pickin', rockabilly, blues, and classic rock. This pickup an excellent match for the ST59-1b lead pickup, providing a total quiet, noise-free setup. The neck Description: Official Limited Edition Fender Deluxe Telecaster Neck & Tuners- Tinted Maple- Modern "C" Shape- 9.5" Radius (241 mm)- 25.5" (648 mm) Scale Length- 1.650" (42 mm) Width at Nut- 21 Medium Jumbo Frets- Genuine Fender Neck has some minor sanding to remove some of the polyurethane off the back for a smoother feel but no change in shape as described. There is a discoloring of the neck on the top facing down as your playing. I Cannot feel this while playing....it’s from the sanding where the satin stain is sanded through. Could be touched up if it bothers you. Also, will include original volume and tone nobs. pick guard is parchment and has some wear from play. Comes with a Deluxe Fender Gig Bag!!
Title: Fender Players Series Telecaster Polar White Guitar With Upgrades
